{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/background-information/risk-factors/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"40a7b32b-318b-593c-a9aa-e04529a85882","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field a0393e08-02fc-4f4e-b44a-66c607262d81 --><h2>What are the risk factors?</h2><!-- end field a0393e08-02fc-4f4e-b44a-66c607262d81 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item d1241dad-5c50-4cc5-a937-a071b52c4bbe --><!-- begin field 3b8529e1-9b4e-4adc-ad4b-f32d1879ed5f --><ul><li><strong>Based on the <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/background-information/pathophysiology/\">pathophysiology</a>, the risk of pilonidal sinus disease may depend on hair type, the force of insertion created within the natal cleft, and the vulnerability of the skin of the natal cleft to hair insertion </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>]<strong>. </strong>Therefore, the risk may be increased in people with:<ul><li>Coarse hair.</li><li>Hirsutism.</li><li>Deep natal cleft.</li><li>Macerated or broken skin.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Other risk factors for the development of pilonidal sinus disease include:</strong><ul><li>Male gender (2–4 times more likely than in women) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kober, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Choy, 2019</a>].</li><li>Age 15–40 years (the mean age at presentation has been reported as 21 years in males and 19 years in females. It is uncommon before puberty and after the age of 45 years) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kober, 2018</a>].</li><li>Being white (more common than in black people, due to different hair characteristics and growth patterns).</li><li>Obesity.</li><li>Poor hygiene.</li><li>Lifestyle or occupation which involves sitting for prolonged periods (more than 6 hours a day) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Harlak, 2010</a>].</li><li>Repetitive trauma to the sacrococcygeal region.</li><li>Family history of pilonidal sinus disease.</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Harlak, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Marza, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Gordon et al, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Segre, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kober, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kuckelman, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Choy, 2019</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Johnson, 2019</a>]</p><!-- end field 3b8529e1-9b4e-4adc-ad4b-f32d1879ed5f --><!-- end item d1241dad-5c50-4cc5-a937-a071b52c4bbe -->","topic":{"id":"c75a0f03-60df-5718-b4ad-d6e32f354f69","topicId":"f6f74445-1669-4cf9-9d42-9881d6be83d1","topicName":"Pilonidal sinus disease","slug":"pilonidal-sinus-disease","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2019","chapters":[{"id":"685753f4-4b6f-54e1-b69e-fafd200dee31","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"5f89fe48-e69a-565c-9208-1e39eafec872","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e102bb7d-89e7-571b-bb6b-e35165528fd8","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"026c97f4-f023-5833-9e34-1248e8d6f2a4","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"fc01babb-9aae-5fad-bc15-f4c9f3652eab","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"03838fc5-29b7-5bfa-bf79-cb6d350d85b3","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"25359572-4486-538a-8f48-2f6546a6cf99","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"2340d6a8-1dbb-5677-8169-4840914c782b","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"c4efc90e-2103-5151-a4dd-e637cfa1b93e","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"78d0ef56-cc49-5a57-b248-fecadb4895d8","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"b5605f6d-767a-5840-abdf-e73045b9577d","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"59438bb8-448a-5bb6-944d-0d001fd58fac","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"59b03a59-8340-516e-b513-a3a39833732d","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"304f3f37-2147-585c-84fb-2dbb1e417738","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"70e5ecd9-dcfe-5b6a-a5d1-3e251a673bd4","slug":"pathophysiology","fullItemName":"Pathophysiology"},{"id":"c6ce3955-0c4a-5f77-9321-bcbe79422612","slug":